# splunk-dns-
A hands-on project using Splunk to analyze DNS logs for threat detection, anomaly identification, and cybersecurity insights. Includes queries, dashboards, and real-world use cases.
#1 SEARCH FOR DNS EVENTS 
index=_* OR index=* sourcetype=dns
#2 COUNTING EVERYTHING 
--lets see how much activity happening, this help us to see internet is busy or free
index=_* OR index=* sourcetype=dns | stats count by _time
--this counts every DNS req and puts it into timeline
#3 TOP IP's
index=_* OR index=* sourcetype=dns | top srcip
--this helps us to find most frequent source ip
#4 TOP DOMIAN
index=_* OR index=* sourcetype=dns | top domain
--this help us to find most visited websites
#5 FILTERING 
index=_* OR index=* sourcetype=dns domain="*arpa" | table _time, srcip, domain
